'''Jens Castrop''' ({{Korean|hangul=옌스 카스트로프}}; born 29 July 2003) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] or [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|wing-back]] for {{German football updater|BoMönche}} club [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

==Club career==
A native of [[Düsseldorf]], Castrop began his career in the youth academy of [[Fortuna Düsseldorf]]. In 2015, he transferred to the academy of Düsseldorf's rival, [[1. FC Köln]], where he played for the club's under-15 and under-17 teams. In August 2020, Castrop was promoted to the club's first team by manager [[Markus Gisdol]]. He also signed a long-term professional contract until June 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/koeln_bindet_17_jaehrigen_castrop_weg_an_den_ich_glaube_-781106/artikel|title=Köln bindet 17-jährigen Castrop: "Weg, an den ich glaube"|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|kicker]]|access-date=14 August 2020}}</ref>

In January 2022, it was announced that Castrop would join [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[1. FC Nürnberg]] on a loan deal.<ref name="BL">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/de/bundesliga/news/1-fc-nurnberg-jens-castrop-1-fc-koln-leihe-transfer-wechsel-18443|title=1. FC Nürnberg leiht Jens Castrop vom 1. FC Köln aus|access-date=7 January 2022|publisher=[[Bundesliga]]|language=de}}</ref> In June 2023, the club activated a €450,000 option to sign Castrop on a permanent basis.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ksta.de/sport/1-fc-koeln/1-fc-koeln-jens-castrop-gefragt-kontert-der-fc-nuernbergs-option-583142 |title=Nürnberg zieht Kaufoption bei Castrop – Kontert Köln? |website=Kölner Stadt-Anzeiger |date=19 June 2023 |language=de}}</ref> At Nürnberg, he was deployed on the right flank of midfield or defensive line during the 2022–23 season,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/jens-castrop/spielerposition/2-bundesliga/2022-23/1-fc-nuernberg |title= Jens Castrop {{!}} Spielerpositionen {{!}} 1. FC Nürnberg {{!}} 2. Bundesliga 2022/23 |publisher=kicker |language=de |access-date=26 August 2025}}</ref> moved to central midfield the next season,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/jens-castrop/spielerposition/2-bundesliga/2023-24/1-fc-nuernberg |title= Jens Castrop {{!}} Spielerpositionen {{!}} 1. FC Nürnberg {{!}} 2. Bundesliga 2023/24 |publisher=kicker |language=de |access-date=26 August 2025}}</ref> and performed the role of left attacking midfielder in 2025.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/jens-castrop/spielerposition/2-bundesliga/2024-25/1-fc-nuernberg |title= Jens Castrop {{!}} Spielerpositionen {{!}} 1. FC Nürnberg {{!}} 2. Bundesliga 2024/25 |publisher=kicker |language=de |access-date=26 August 2025}}</ref>

On 2 February 2025, Castrop signed a four-season contract with [[Bundesliga]] side [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]], beginning in the 2025–26 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Borussia Mönchengladbach|url=https://www.borussia.com/news/jens-castrop-to-join-borussia-ahead-of-2025-26-season|title=Jens Castrop to join Borussia ahead of 2025/26 season|date=2 February 2025|access-date=30 June 2025}}</ref> On 27 September, he scored his first Bundesliga goal in a 6–4 loss to [[Eintracht Frankfurt]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/matchday/2025-2026/5/borussia-moenchengladbach-vs-eintracht-frankfurt/liveticker |title=Borussia Mönchengladbach - Eintracht Frankfurt {{!}} 2025/26 Season |publisher=Bundesliga |access-date=2025-09-28}}</ref> Borussia had a hard time without a win at the bottom of the league early in the season, but he was named the club's Player of the Month for September.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.borussia.com/news/castrop-potm-september-2526 |title=Jens Castrop is Borussia's Player of the Month for September |publisher=Borussia Mönchengladbach |date=2025-10-01 |access-date=2025-10-04}}</ref> On 25 October, he received his first red card at the Bundesliga after tackling [[Luis Díaz (footballer, born 1997)|Luis Díaz]] in a 3–0 loss to [[Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bavarianfootballworks.com/bayern-munich-bundesliga/144957/jens-castrop-apologetic-red-card-borussia-monchengladbach-bayern-munich-gladbach-bundesliga-luis-diaz |title=Gladbach's Jens Castrop apologetic for red card in loss to Bayern Munich |publisher=Bavarian Football Works |date=2025-10-26 |access-date=2025-10-26}}</ref> On 21 March 2026, he scored two goals while playing as a left wing-back in a 3–3 draw with 1. FC Köln.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/matchday/2025-2026/27/1-fc-koeln-vs-borussia-moenchengladbach/lineup |title=
Cologne - Borussia Mönchengladbach {{!}} 2025/26 Season |publisher=Bundesliga |access-date=2026-03-22}}</ref>

==International career==
Castrop was born in Germany to a German father and South Korean mother.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.getfootballnewsgermany.com/2025/fifa-approve-jens-castrops-switch-of-allegiance-to-south-korea/ |title=FIFA approve Jens Castrop's switch of allegiance to South Korea |publisher=Get German Football News |date=12 August 2025}}</ref> He played for [[Germany national youth football team|Germany national youth teams]] at between under-16 and under-21 level before being affiliated to [[Korea Football Association]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dfb.de/datencenter/personen/jens-castrop/spieler/spiele-in-saison/bundesliga-west-1736/2018-2019/1-fc-koeln-u-17 |title=Jens Castrop – Spielerprofil |publisher=DFB |access-date=14 August 2020}}</ref> His request to switch international allegiance to South Korea was approved by [[FIFA]] on 11 August 2025,<ref name="FIFA-Change">{{Cite web |url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform |title=FIFA Change of Association Platform |publisher=FIFA |accessdate=12 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/fifa-bestaetigt-castrop-wechselt-verband-und-hofft-auf-einsaetze-mit-son-1137804/artikel |title=FIFA bestätigt: Castrop wechselt Verband und hofft auf Einsätze mit Son |language=de |publisher=kicker |date=12 August 2025}}</ref> and he was called up to the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]] for friendlies held in September.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kfa.or.kr/layer_popup/popup_live.php?act=news_tv_detail&idx=27371&div_code=news&check_url=bGF5ZXI=&lang=KOR |script-title=ko:'카스트로프 발탁' 남자 A대표팀, 9월 A매치 명단 발표 |language=ko |publisher=KFA |date=25 August 2025 |access-date=25 August 2025}}</ref> On 6 September, he came on as a 63rd-minute substitute in a 2–0 win over the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]], making his senior international debut.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://m-en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20250907000200315 |title=S. Korea beat U.S. in men's football friendly behind Son's goal, assist |publisher=Yonhap News Agency |date=7 September 2025 |access-date=7 September 2025}}</ref>

